# EduStream — Database Schema & API Architecture Design

---

## 1. Project Understanding

EduStream is an **educational content platform** consisting of two applications:

| Component | Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| **Admin Panel** | Laravel (Blade UI) | Content management, user management, order tracking, analytics |
| **Mobile App** | Flutter | Student-facing app for browsing courses, watching videos, taking quizzes, purchasing content |

**Current State**: Both applications have **static UI only** — no backend logic, no database, no API integration. All data is hardcoded in views and Dart models.

**Business Model**: The platform sells educational content organized by school standards (Nursery through Std 10). Content can be purchased as full courses, individual subjects, or custom bundles. Content items (notes, videos, quizzes) can be individually marked as free or paid.

---

## 2. UI Feature Analysis

### Admin Panel Features (from Blade views)

| Page | Key Features | Data Implications |
|---|---|---|
| **Dashboard** | Stats: total students, content items, enrollments, quizzes, revenue; Recent enrollments table; Activity feed | Aggregated counts from multiple tables |
| **Login** | Email + password login, remember me, forgot password | `users` table with admin credentials |
| **Categories** | CRUD for education categories (Primary, Secondary, etc.) with course counts | `categories` table |
| **Courses** | CRUD with: title, icon, color, category, price, status, description, thumbnail | `courses` table linked to categories |
| **Subjects** | CRUD within a course: name, icon, color, price, status, description | `subjects` table linked to courses |
| **Notes Manager** | Folder-based file manager; upload PDF/DOC; free/paid toggle; title, description, thumbnail, sort order | `notes` + `note_folders` tables |
| **Videos Manager** | Same folder structure; upload video; duration; free/paid toggle; title, description, thumbnail, sort order | `videos` + `video_folders` tables |
| **QA Papers Manager** | Same folder pattern; upload question papers; free/paid toggle | `qa_papers` + `qa_paper_folders` tables |
| **Quiz Manager** | List quizzes per subject; status toggle; free/paid; quiz builder with MCQ/TF/Short Answer | `quizzes` + `quiz_questions` + `quiz_options` tables |
| **Quiz Builder** | Question text, type (MCQ/TF/Short), options with correct answer marking, marks per question, time per question; Settings: total time, total marks, pass %, max attempts, shuffle, show results, pricing | Extended quiz schema with settings |
| **Users/Students** | List: name, email, plan (premium/free), status (active/blocked), enrollment date, courses count; Actions: view, block/unblock, export | `users` table with role/plan fields |
| **Orders/Enrollments** | List: enrollment ID, student, course, date, amount, payment method (UPI/Card/Net Banking), status (enrolled/pending/cancelled/refunded); Filters by status and date; Manual enrollment | `enrollments` + `payments` tables |
| **Analytics** | Dashboard analytics (placeholder) | Aggregation queries |
| **Settings** | Platform settings (placeholder) | `settings` table |

### Flutter App Features (from Dart screens/models)

| Screen | Key Features | Data Implications |
|---|---|---|
| **Splash → Auth** | Mobile number login, OTP verification, signup with name/email/mobile | Mobile-first auth with OTP |
| **Home** | Recent content cards, quiz cards, upgrade banner | Personalized content based on enrollment |
| **Explore Standards** | Browse by category (Primary/Middle School/High School) → Standards list | `categories` → `courses` hierarchy |
| **Standard Detail** | Subject cards within a standard; Purchase options: full course, individual subject, custom bundle | Flexible purchase model |
| **Course Preview** | Preview content tree before purchase; See folders, videos, notes, tests in tree structure | `content_items` hierarchy with preview access |
| **Subject Detail** | View content for a purchased subject | Access control per enrollment |
| **Video Player** | Play video lectures (uploaded + demo) | Video file storage path |
| **Notes Screen** | View/download PDF notes | File download URLs |
| **Quiz List** | Available quizzes with difficulty, duration, attempts used/max; Free/paid badges | Quiz access tied to enrollment |
| **Quiz Attempt** | Take quiz: display questions, options, timer; Submit and see results | `quiz_attempts` + `quiz_answers` tables |
| **Cart** | Add full course / individual subject / custom bundle; Checkout | `cart_items` → `orders` flow |
| **Checkout** | Payment processing | Payment gateway integration point |
| **My Courses** | View enrolled/purchased courses | User enrollments query |
| **Profile** | User profile management | User profile data |
| **Live Class** | Live class feature (placeholder) | Future `live_classes` table |

---

## 3. System Architecture

```
┌─────────────────────┐    ┌───────────────────────┐
│   Admin Panel        │    │    Flutter App          │
│   (Laravel Blade)    │    │    (Dart/Flutter)       │
│                      │    │                         │
│  - Session Auth      │    │  - JWT Auth             │
│  - Server-rendered   │    │  - API Consumer         │
└──────────┬───────────┘    └──────────┬──────────────┘
           │                           │
           │  Web Requests             │  REST API (JSON)
           │  (Session/CSRF)           │  (Bearer JWT Token)
           │                           │
           ▼                           ▼
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              Laravel API Backend                      │
│                                                       │
│  ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────────┐    ┌────────────┐  │
│  │Controller │───▶│ Service Layer │───▶│  Repository │  │
│  │  (Thin)   │    │  (Business   │    │  (Eloquent  │  │
│  │           │    │   Logic)     │    │   Models)   │  │
│  └──────────┘    └──────────────┘    └──────┬─────┘  │
│                                              │        │
│  ┌──────────────┐    ┌───────────────────┐   │        │
│  │ Middleware    │    │ File Storage       │   │        │
│  │ (Auth, CORS, │    │ (Local / S3)       │   │        │
│  │  Rate Limit) │    └───────────────────┘   │        │
│  └──────────────┘                            │        │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────┼────────┘
                                               │
                                               ▼
                                    ┌──────────────────┐
                                    │    MySQL / PgSQL  │
                                    │    Database       │
                                    └──────────────────┘
```

### Layer Responsibilities

| Layer | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| **Controllers** | Validate input, call service, return response. **No business logic.** |
| **Services** | All business logic: enrollment rules, pricing calculations, access control, file management |
| **Repositories / Models** | Database queries via Eloquent ORM. Relationships, scopes, accessors |
| **Middleware** | JWT validation (app API), session auth (admin), CORS, rate limiting |
| **File Storage** | Laravel filesystem abstraction for notes/videos/QA papers (local or S3) |

### Admin Panel Flow
- Uses **Laravel session authentication** (standard web auth)
- Server-side rendered Blade views with CSRF protection
- Admin-only access, no JWT needed

### Flutter App Flow
- Uses **JWT authentication** via REST API
- All requests include `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header
- Stateless API, no sessions

---

## 4. Database Schema

### Authentication Module

---

#### Table: `admins`

**Purpose**: Stores admin panel users who manage the platform via the Laravel admin panel.

| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `id` | `BIGINT UNSIGNED` | PK, AUTO_INCREMENT | |
| `name` | `VARCHAR(255)` | NOT NULL | Full name |
| `email` | `VARCHAR(255)` | UNIQUE, NOT NULL | Login email |
| `password` | `VARCHAR(255)` | NOT NULL | Hashed password |
| `avatar_url` | `VARCHAR(500)` | NULLABLE | Profile photo URL |
| `status` | `ENUM('active','inactive')` | DEFAULT 'active' | |
| `remember_token` | `VARCHAR(100)` | NULLABLE | Laravel remember me |
| `created_at` | `TIMESTAMP` | | |
| `updated_at` | `TIMESTAMP` | | |

**Indexes**: `email` (unique)

**Relationships**:
- Has many `activity_logs`

---

#### Table: `students`

**Purpose**: Stores mobile app students who consume educational content via the Flutter app.

| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `id` | `BIGINT UNSIGNED` | PK, AUTO_INCREMENT | |
| `name` | `VARCHAR(255)` | NOT NULL | Full name |
| `email` | `VARCHAR(255)` | NULLABLE | Optional email |
| `mobile` | `VARCHAR(15)` | UNIQUE, NOT NULL | Login via OTP |
| `avatar_url` | `VARCHAR(500)` | NULLABLE | Profile photo URL |
| `plan` | `ENUM('free','premium')` | DEFAULT 'free' | Subscription plan |
| `status` | `ENUM('active','blocked')` | DEFAULT 'active' | |
| `mobile_verified_at` | `TIMESTAMP` | NULLABLE | OTP verification timestamp |
| `created_at` | `TIMESTAMP` | | |
| `updated_at` | `TIMESTAMP` | | |

**Indexes**: `mobile` (unique), `status`, `plan`

**Relationships**:
- Has many `enrollments`
- Has many `quiz_attempts`
- Has many `refresh_tokens`

---

#### Table: `refresh_tokens`

**Purpose**: Stores JWT refresh tokens for mobile app authentication.

| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `id` | `BIGINT UNSIGNED` | PK, AUTO_INCREMENT | |
| `student_id` | `BIGINT UNSIGNED` | FK → `students.id`, ON DELETE CASCADE | |
| `token` | `VARCHAR(500)` | UNIQUE, NOT NULL | Hashed refresh token |
| `device_name` | `VARCHAR(255)` | NULLABLE | e.g. "Samsung Galaxy S23" |
| `device_id` | `VARCHAR(255)` | NULLABLE | Unique device identifier |
| `expires_at` | `TIMESTAMP` | NOT NULL | Token expiration |
| `revoked_at` | `TIMESTAMP` | NULLABLE | NULL = active; set when revoked |
| `created_at` | `TIMESTAMP` | | |

**Indexes**: `token` (unique), `student_id`, `expires_at`

---

#### Table: `otp_verifications`

**Purpose**: Temporary OTP storage for mobile authentication.

| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `id` | `BIGINT UNSIGNED` | PK, AUTO_INCREMENT | |
| `mobile` | `VARCHAR(15)` | NOT NULL | Mobile number |
| `otp` | `VARCHAR(10)` | NOT NULL | Hashed OTP code |
| `purpose` | `ENUM('login','signup','reset')` | NOT NULL | |
| `attempts` | `TINYINT` | DEFAULT 0 | Failed verification attempts |
| `expires_at` | `TIMESTAMP` | NOT NULL | OTP validity (typically 5 mins) |
| `verified_at` | `TIMESTAMP` | NULLABLE | |
| `created_at` | `TIMESTAMP` | | |

**Indexes**: `mobile`, `expires_at`

---

### Content Module

---

#### Table: `categories`

**Purpose**: Top-level grouping for courses (e.g., Primary, Middle School, High School).

| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `id` | `BIGINT UNSIGNED` | PK, AUTO_INCREMENT | |
| `name` | `VARCHAR(255)` | NOT NULL, UNIQUE | e.g. "Primary School", "High School" |
| `slug` | `VARCHAR(255)` | NOT NULL, UNIQUE | URL-safe identifier |
| `sort_order` | `INT` | DEFAULT 0 | Display ordering |
| `created_at` | `TIMESTAMP` | | |
| `updated_at` | `TIMESTAMP` | | |

**Relationships**:
- Has many `courses`

---

#### Table: `courses`

**Purpose**: Represents a standard/course (e.g., "Standard 10", "BCA Semester 1"). This is the primary purchasable unit in the admin panel.

| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `id` | `BIGINT UNSIGNED` | PK, AUTO_INCREMENT | |
| `category_id` | `BIGINT UNSIGNED` | FK → `categories.id`, ON DELETE RESTRICT | |
| `name` | `VARCHAR(255)` | NOT NULL | e.g. "Standard 10" |
| `slug` | `VARCHAR(255)` | NOT NULL, UNIQUE | |
| `description` | `TEXT` | NULLABLE | Course overview |
| `icon` | `VARCHAR(100)` | NULLABLE | FontAwesome class: "fa-solid fa-graduation-cap" |
| `color` | `VARCHAR(10)` | DEFAULT '#1565C0' | Hex color for theming |
| `price` | `DECIMAL(10,2)` | NOT NULL, DEFAULT 0 | Full course price in ₹ |
| `thumbnail_url` | `VARCHAR(500)` | NULLABLE | Course thumbnail image path |
| `status` | `ENUM('active','inactive')` | NOT NULL, DEFAULT 'active' | |
| `sort_order` | `INT` | DEFAULT 0 | |
| `created_at` | `TIMESTAMP` | | |
| `updated_at` | `TIMESTAMP` | | |

**Indexes**: `category_id`, `status`, `slug` (unique)

**Relationships**:
- Belongs to `category`
- Has many `subjects`
- Has many `enrollments`

---

#### Table: `subjects`

**Purpose**: A subject within a course (e.g., "Mathematics" under "Standard 10"). Can be purchased individually or as part of a course.

| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `id` | `BIGINT UNSIGNED` | PK, AUTO_INCREMENT | |
| `course_id` | `BIGINT UNSIGNED` | FK → `courses.id`, ON DELETE CASCADE | |
| `name` | `VARCHAR(255)` | NOT NULL | e.g. "Mathematics" |
| `slug` | `VARCHAR(255)` | NOT NULL | Unique within course |
| `description` | `TEXT` | NULLABLE | |
| `icon` | `VARCHAR(100)` | NULLABLE | FontAwesome class |
| `color` | `VARCHAR(10)` | DEFAULT '#1565C0' | |
| `price` | `DECIMAL(10,2)` | NOT NULL, DEFAULT 0 | Individual subject price |
| `status` | `ENUM('active','inactive')` | NOT NULL, DEFAULT 'active' | |
| `sort_order` | `INT` | DEFAULT 0 | |
| `created_at` | `TIMESTAMP` | | |
| `updated_at` | `TIMESTAMP` | | |

**Indexes**: `course_id`, `status`, composite unique [(course_id, slug)](file:///c:/Flutter/edustream/lib/features/home/presentation/screens/home_screen.dart#36-71)

**Relationships**:
- Belongs to `course`
- Has many `note_folders`, `video_folders`, `qa_paper_folders`
- Has many `notes`, `videos`, `qa_papers`
- Has many `quizzes`

---

#### Table: `note_folders`

**Purpose**: Hierarchical folder structure for organizing notes (PDF/DOC) within each subject. Supports nested folders.

| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `id` | `BIGINT UNSIGNED` | PK, AUTO_INCREMENT | |
| `subject_id` | `BIGINT UNSIGNED` | FK → `subjects.id`, ON DELETE CASCADE | |
| `parent_id` | `BIGINT UNSIGNED` | FK → `note_folders.id`, NULLABLE | NULL = root folder |
| `name` | `VARCHAR(255)` | NOT NULL | e.g. "Chapter 1 - Algebra" |
| `description` | `TEXT` | NULLABLE | |
| `thumbnail_url` | `VARCHAR(500)` | NULLABLE | |
| `sort_order` | `INT` | DEFAULT 0 | |
| `created_at` | `TIMESTAMP` | | |
| `updated_at` | `TIMESTAMP` | | |

**Indexes**: `subject_id`, `parent_id`

**Relationships**:
- Belongs to `subject`
- Belongs to `parent` (self-referencing)
- Has many `children` folders
- Has many `notes`

---

#### Table: `notes`

**Purpose**: Stores note files (PDF, DOC, TXT). Each note belongs to a subject and optionally a note folder.

| Column | Type | Constraints | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `id` | `BIGINT UNSIGNED` | PK, AUTO_INCREMENT | |
| `subject_id` | `BIGINT UNSIGNED` | FK → `subjects.id`, ON DELETE CASCADE | |
| `folder_id` | `BIGINT UNSIGNED` | FK → `note_folders.id`, NULLABLE | NULL = root level |
| `title` | `VARCHAR(255)` | NOT NULL | Display title |
| `description` | `TEXT` | NULLABLE | |
| `file_name` | `VARCHAR(255)` | NOT NULL | Original filename |
| `file_path` | `VARCHAR(500)` | NOT NULL | Storage path (local or S3 key) |
| `file_size` | `BIGINT` | NULLABLE | Size in bytes |
| `mime_type` | `VARCHAR(100)` | NULLABLE | e.g. "application/pdf", "application/msword" |
| `thumbnail_url` | `VARCHAR(500)` | NULLABLE | Optional custom thumbnail |
| `is_free` | `BOOLEAN` | DEFAULT false | Free = accessible without purchase |
| `sort_order` | `INT` | DEFAULT 0 | |
| `status` | `ENUM('active','inactive')` | DEFAULT 'active' | |
| `created_at` | `TIMESTAMP` | | |
| `updated_at` | `TIMESTAMP` | | |

**Indexes**: `subject_id`, `folder_id`, `is_free`, `status`

**Relationships**:
- Belongs to `subject`
- Belongs to `note_folder` (optional)

---

