## 8. Table Relationships

```
categories
  └── has many → courses
                   ├── has many → subjects
                   │                ├── has many → note_folders (self-ref parent_id)
                   │                │                └── has many → notes
                   │                ├── has many → video_folders (self-ref parent_id)
                   │                │                └── has many → videos
                   │                ├── has many → qa_paper_folders (self-ref parent_id)
                   │                │                └── has many → qa_papers
                   │                └── has many → quizzes
                   │                                 ├── has many → quiz_questions
                   │                                 │                └── has many → quiz_options
                   │                                 └── has many → quiz_attempts
                   │                                                  └── has many → quiz_answers
                   ├── has many → order_items
                   ├── has many → cart_items
                   └── has many → enrollments

admins
  └── has many → activity_logs

students
  ├── has many → orders
  │                └── has many → order_items
  ├── has many → enrollments
  ├── has many → cart_items
  ├── has many → quiz_attempts
  └── has many → refresh_tokens
```

---

## 9. Module-Based Table Organization

### Authentication Module (4 tables)

| Table | Why It Exists |
|---|---|
| `admins` | Admin panel users — email + password login, session auth |
| `students` | Mobile app users — mobile + OTP login, JWT auth |
| `refresh_tokens` | JWT token lifecycle management for Flutter app |
| `otp_verifications` | Temporary OTP codes for mobile-first passwordless auth |

### Content Module (9 tables)

| Table | Why It Exists |
|---|---|
| `categories` | Top-level organization (Primary School, High School, etc.) |
| `courses` | The main educational unit — a standard or degree program |
| `subjects` | Individual subjects within a course, each independently purchasable |
| `note_folders` | Hierarchical folder structure for organizing notes within subjects |
| `notes` | Study material files — PDF, DOC, TXT |
| `video_folders` | Hierarchical folder structure for organizing videos within subjects |
| `videos` | Video lecture files — MP4, with duration tracking |
| `qa_paper_folders` | Hierarchical folder structure for organizing QA papers within subjects |
| `qa_papers` | Question/answer papers — PDF, DOC |

### Quiz Module (4 tables)

| Table | Why It Exists |
|---|---|
| `quizzes` | Quiz metadata and settings (time, marks, attempts, etc.) |
| `quiz_questions` | Individual questions with type (MCQ/TF/Short) |
| `quiz_options` | MCQ answer choices with correct marking |
| `quiz_attempts` | Student attempt records with scoring |
| `quiz_answers` | Individual answers per attempt for review/analytics |

### Commerce Module (4 tables)

| Table | Why It Exists |
|---|---|
| `cart_items` | Student's transient shopping session |
| `orders` | The checkout/payment transaction wrapper |
| `order_items` | The individual courses/subjects bought in the order |
| `enrollments` | Translates a completed order into content access |

### System Module (2 tables)

| Table | Why It Exists |
|---|---|
| `activity_logs` | Audit trail for dashboard feed and admin activity tracking |
| `settings` | Key-value configuration store for platform settings |

